# entity

Entity:
- render() -> LivingEntityPart.render(), EffectEntityPart.render()

EntityPart:
- LivingEntityPart
	- getHealth()
	- private animation
		-> getImageID()
	- getPlayerStats()
	- getKD()
	- getPlayerProperties()
	- getName()
	- getRank()
	- getTeam()
	- getHealth()

- PhysicsEntityPart
	- Mass
	- CollisionDetection
	- MenuPosition
	- MenuSize
- EffectEntityPart
	- What effects are possible
	- List<Effect>
	- getEffectsOnOff()

Examples:
- Stonetile (NoLivingEntityPart, SolidPhysicsEntityPart, ImmuneEffectEntityPart)
- Watertile (NoLivingEntityPart, NeutralPhysicsEntityPart, WaterEffectEntityPart)
- Breakable Tile (BreakableTileLivingEntityPart, SolidPhysicsEntityPart (collidable -> damage), ImmuneEffectEntityPart)
- ServerGamePlayer (PlayerLivingEntityPart, DynamicPhysicsEntityPart, CreatureEffectEntityPart)
- ServerGamePlayer (FireMage) (PlayerLivingEntityPart, DynamicPhysicsEntityPart, CreatureEffectEntityPart/FireEffectEntityPart)
- Arrow (NoLivingEntityPart, DynamicPhysicsEntityPart, WoodEffectEntityPart)
- Hitbox (NoLivingEntityPart, Static/Dynamic-PhysicsEntityPart, ImmuneEffectEntityPart)
- Particle (NoLivingEntityPart, NeutralPhysicsEntityPart, ImmuneEffectEntityPart)
- IceShard (NoLivingEntityPart, DynamicPhysicsEntityPart, IceEffectEntityPart)
- WaterSplash (NoLivingEntityPart, DynamicPhysicsEntityPart, WaterEffectEntityPart)
- ExplodingSnowball (ActOnDieLivingEntityPart, DynamicPhysicsEntityPart, IceEffectEntityPart)


EntityParts are the 3 units a Entity is made of (LivingEntityPart, PhysicsEntityPart, EffectEntityPart)

There are create{Living,Physics,Effect}EntityPart()-functions in every Entity-(sub)class,
they return the EntityParts to set in the Entity constructor.

EntityPart-subclasses can implement EnityPartProperties to achieve new functionalities.
e.g. 	every LivingEntityPart that can die, has to implement MortalLivingEntityPart to have access to the die()-function.
	if health is <= 0, the entity checks if it is a MortalLivingEntityPart. and if it is: it executes die().jj
